answer: "Do not store images in database" is just another wrong generalization, like this one itself. Well, it is probably not a good idea to store all public members photos/avatars in a database but let's say you want to store only your employees photos and you have <20 employee AND you do NOT want to setup a web server or some kind of "file-sharing" AND ALSO your application supports remote management. Guess what, storing the images in database is your one-and-only best shot!
